{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 No child should ever be subjected to the trauma of being touched by a drug-addicted adult. I've been there, and no child deserves to be scarred for life by drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The best way to decrease drug abuse is to create a society where people are not addicted to drugs in the first place.'}
{'text': 'Advocates of legalization argue that it will reduce the amount of drugs that are available on the street. They claim that this will result in a decrease in the amount of addicts.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 My fellow Americans, please believe me when I say that I am truly sorry for everything I have done, and everything I will do, to protect you from the horrors of the drug war.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The ultimate goal of drug law reform is not to eliminate drugs, but to reduce the amount of money and resources spent on anti-drug efforts.'}
{'text': "If you're someone who is against drug abuse, then why do you say that legalization will lead to more illegality? Is it because you think that the government should control drugs?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's talk about the legalization of drugs when it comes to alcohol, tobacco, and other addictive substances."}
{'text': "If you like the way drugs are currently being used and want them to remain so, then why aren't you taking part in the effort to reform the drug laws?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we really want to reduce drug abuse, it's not enough to get people to stop using drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 There are far too many people in this world that struggle with addiction and mental illness.'}
{'text': 'Narcotics laws exist to protect us from ourselves. If you are not a criminal, then you cannot be a criminal.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It would be beneficial for the people to have access to drugs, but let me ask you, do you want to work in an underpaid, exploitative profession?'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 By legalizing drugs, we are limiting the damage caused by drug use, so we are reducing the costs of enforcing the drug laws, and we are freeing up government resources for other important things.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why do we need a drug war? What's the point of prohibiting something so harmless as marijuana?"}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It would be nice if the government would just get out of the way and let people do what they want with their own bodies.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Drug use is going down. We shouldn't be surprised that this is the case."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The legalization of drugs will not reduce the amount of drugs that are available on the street. This is just another way in which the prohibition of drugs causes more harm to people than it prevents.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The United States has some of the most restrictive drug laws in the world. I mean, come on, the US can't even have federal gun control laws that prevent citizens from owning guns."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If the government didn't interfere with drug use, why would we even be having this conversation in the first place?"}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalization of drugs will allow drug cartels to exist. It will also allow some of these cartels to profit from selling drugs.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It is wrong for someone to take drugs under any circumstances. The so-called drug war has only resulted in more problems and more people being harmed by drugs.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if we decriminalize our drug laws, but still leave them in place?'}
{'text': "We don't want to legalize drugs, we want to decriminalize them. People aren't going to stop using drugs if there's no penalties attached to using them."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't know about anyone else, but I actually enjoy marijuana and other drugs."}
{'text': "People already use drugs. If they aren't punished for it, why should they be punished for using it?"}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I've seen too many young, black men in my life who, because of the justice system, were forced to grow up believing that they were nothing more than human garbage."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Imagine if it were possible to legally grow and sell marijuana all over the country. Would there be an increase in marijuana use?'}
{'text': "If we legalized drugs, wouldn't we then have to legalize alcohol, tobacco, and other drugs too? Isn't that kind of a waste of time?"}
{'text': 'In the end, this debate is not about morality, it\'s about money. To quote Albert Einstein, "Religion makes fools of men who should know better.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I don't think we need a total legalization of drugs."}
{'text': 'In terms of health risks, there is absolutely no evidence to suggest that the decriminalization of drugs will result in a decrease in the amount of drugs available on the street.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I am not sure that this is the best way to go about this.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It might be a good idea to legalize drugs solely for medicinal purposes. After all, when I was a teenager, I smoked pot occasionally.'}
{'text': "People are being too quick to give up their right to privacy and personal freedom. These are very important rights that shouldn't be relinquished lightly."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalization of drugs would create the opportunity for a host of people to get out of the worst kinds of bad jobs. Most of these jobs would be in the illegal drug trade.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 When I was in high school, I was heavily into drugs and alcohol.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What happens to those who are addicted to marijuana? Will they still have to deal with the stigma associated with using drugs? Will they still be discriminated against when it comes to getting jobs?'}
{'text': "People are not likely to stop using drugs if they're not penalized for doing so. The only way to reduce the amount of drugs available on the street is to tax them."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's legalize all drugs except for alcohol and tobacco. This way we'll be able to prevent people from becoming addicted to them in the first place."}
{'text': 'It is possible that the legalization of drugs could lead to a decrease in the amount of addictive drugs that are available on the street.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not let the government decide what drugs are legal and what drugs are not?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's focus our energies on the less harmful drugs first, like alcohol. There are a lot of people out there who need help."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What do you think would happen to the economy if people were allowed to legally smoke cigarettes, drink alcohol, and use illegal drugs?'}
{'text': 'It is wrong for someone to smoke marijuana under any circumstances. The so called drug war has only resulted in more problems and more people being harmed by drugs.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalizing drugs would be a good thing, but it wouldn't solve the whole problem. I don't see the need to make it easier for people to use drugs."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 As long as there's a huge profit incentive built into the drug industry, drug use will continue."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 For anyone who doesn't know, marijuana is used for medicinal purposes. It could be an alternative to prescription painkillers."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 How do you feel about having sex with animals? In terms of risk, is it any different from using drugs?'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We are talking about creating a whole new set of moral principles when we talk about legalizing drugs, which means that we're going to need a whole new set of moral principles when we talk about..."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If certain drugs are made legal, then other, less harmful drugs will also be made legal. This will cause an increase in the number of people experimenting with other drugs.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 This is not the time to legalize drugs. At this moment, we need to focus on finding a way to help America's youth get educated."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you want to stop drug abuse, then you have to make it illegal to use drugs. That's it."}
{'text': "What if it's not drugs, but the violence and lawlessness that accompanies prohibition? Is that not worthy of abolishing as well?"}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The problem with marijuana is that it is a psychoactive drug. What this means is that when someone uses marijuana, he or she is altering their state of mind.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 It doesn't really matter what type of drug you smoke, as long as you aren't breaking any laws."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Marijuana users should not be punished for their recreational use of the drug.'}
{'text': 'If we legalize drugs, there will be more illegal drugs available to us.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If someone has made a mistake, give them a second chance. Use the opportunity to help them get sober and improve their life. Give them a second chance.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 A nation that can't afford to have a great public education system cannot afford to let people who know how to make money off of this knowledge go to jail."}

{'text': 'I think it would be great if instead of trying to legalize drugs, it was easier to just decriminalize them, which would logically mean fewer criminals involved in the manufacture and distribution of drugs.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Because drug abuse is a problem, though, we should take action to deal with it.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Just because a drug is illegal, doesn't mean that it can't be used."}
{'text': "If we really want to reduce the amount of addictive drugs that are available on the street, it's not enough to get people to stop using drugs."}
{'text': "If you're going to advocate for the legalization of drugs, then you need to advocate for its legalization for medicinal purposes."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What's wrong with decriminalizing all drugs? Legalizing all drugs would mean that nobody in their right mind would want to buy illegal drugs."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The only way to decrease the amount of drugs available on the street is for the government to tax them.'}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we really want to help our youth, we're going to have to find a way to deal with the effects of the criminal justice system and the environment in which our children grow up."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we really want to reduce drug abuse, it's not enough to get people to stop using drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Drug use is going down. We shouldn't be surprised that this is the case. That's the way it should be.\xa0 Everyone who is concerned about drugs should be concerned about this."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 The normalization of drug use has a negative effect on society. It leads to a general decrease in the quality of life and in the general moral foundation of society.'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's go ahead and legalize drugs. In theory, it would reduce the amount of violence in the United States."}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why should we have to choose between raising taxes and having unlimited access to drugs?'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 We now live in a society in which almost all the people want to be rich.'}
{'text': "Just because a drug is illegal, doesn't mean that it can't be used."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you legalize drugs, you'll have to deal with the fact that cannabis is still illegal."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What if we didn't have laws against drugs and instead regulated them?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 How can you expect to solve a problem if you're not even willing to think about it?"}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why don't we just tax the people who buy drugs?"}
{'text': "I'm all in favor of legalization of drugs, but do you know why? Because the current system is failing us. Drug prohibition is a failed policy."}
{'text': "Legalization doesn't necessarily mean less criminals involved in the manufacturing and distribution of drugs."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 So, how can we prevent someone from abusing substances? The easiest way to do this is to legalize them so that we don't have to punish people for using them."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 First off, I hope that the big corporations that support the war on drugs are smart enough to see that legalization will lead to an increase in profits.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not also legalize the sale of alcohol, which is also a highly addictive drug that leads to a lot of violence and property damage?'}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Let's discuss legalization of drugs! That seems to be the most sensible way to handle this problem."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Legalization of drugs would also provide an extra boost to drug rehabilitation centers around the country. When people aren't using drugs, they can spend more time with their families."}
{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 I think it's a good idea, but I think it's a good idea that the government shouldn't be involved in the drug trade at all."}

{'text': "\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If we legalized alcohol, tobacco and other drugs, wouldn't we then have to legalize gambling as well? Aren't those activities just as harmful as drugs? Aren't they just as immoral?"}
{'text': "I'm not a fan of the idea of legalizing drugs. However, I do believe that we need to focus our efforts in solving the problem of drug abuse, rather than trying to legalize drugs."}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 If you really want to make a change in the world for the better, then you need to start at the very bottom and work your way up. Not the other way around.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Why not legalize money and gambling? After all, they are both used to buy food, drink and clothes.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 In the past, drug use has been banned in many countries.'}
{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 Our government needs to focus resources on eliminating the demand for drugs, instead of legalizing them.'}

{'text': '\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0 What happens to people who are addicted to heroin, cocaine, methamphetamine, etc? Will they still have to deal with the stigma associated with using drugs?'}
